When configuring docket, an option is available to provide class definitions to ignore.

     @Bean
    public Docket api() {
        return new Docket(DocumentationType.SWAGGER_2)
                .ignoredParameterTypes(Authentication.class)
                .select()
                .apis(RequestHandlerSelectors.withClassAnnotation(RestController.class))
                .paths(PathSelectors.any())
                .build();
    }


**Note:** `.ignoredParameterTypes(Authentication.class)` where *Authentication.class* refers to *org.springframework.security.core.Authentication*.  Helpfull when injecting various contexts into controller methods which are irrelevant to the api user.

